[Task Recognition Skill]
Detect when the user is creating, listing, updating, blocking, rescheduling, or completing actionable work.

Purpose:
- Turn user TODO language into persistent TODO tracking only when the user actually wants durable task state.
- Route any time-triggered, recurring, scheduled, reminder-at-a-time, or assistant-background job request into the V4 Scheduler job tool instead of the user TODO tool.

When to use:
- Treat explicit TODOs, follow-ups, blockers, status updates, and completion updates as user task-management work.
- Treat any request that includes trigger time, recurrence, "tomorrow at", "every day", "every week", scheduled reminder, or scheduled execution as assistant scheduled-task work.
- Activate when the user wants to create, inspect, update, or complete tracked items instead of keeping everything in free-form chat.

Tool paths:
- manage_tasks for persisted user TODO creation, listing, status changes, and completion.
- manage_scheduled_jobs for assistant-owned single-run or recurring scheduled work backed by Core Scheduler.

Boundaries:
- When the user only wants planning advice without tracking, answer directly and avoid unnecessary task writes.
- Do not use manage_tasks for anything with trigger time or frequency.
- Do not imply that a TODO or scheduled task exists unless the corresponding tool confirms the stored state.
